                                      muKern v.1.0.062026

A minimal microkernel design for x86_64, ARMv8-A and RV64, 
plus a working proof-of-concept that boots on all three
and drops you into a tiny serial REPL.

DESIGN 

Minimal Trusted Computing Base (TCB): The kernel code must be small enough 
(ideally <10,000 lines) to be mentally manageable and formally verifiable. It handles 
only threads, address spaces, and IPC.

Synchronous IPC: Inter-Process Communication is the backbone. It must be extremely fast 
(register-based message passing) to minimize the cost of crossing protection domains.

Capability-Based Security: Access to resources (memory, devices, other processes) is 
granted exclusively via unforgeable tokens (capabilities) passed through IPC. There are
no global namespaces.

External Paging: The kernel manages physical memory allocation but does not decide which
pages to swap or map. User-space "Page Servers" handle policy decisions like demand paging.

Fault Isolation: Drivers and filesystems run in user mode. If a driver crashes, the kernel
remains intact, and a monitor process can restart the driver without rebooting the system. 

